      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I think we are missing some connections here. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First, Mayong &amp;quot;was&amp;quot; a demi-god already before he was killed.  Hence the demi-plane of blood and shadowspine (i think they are the same place though but i might be wrong...pulling a lot of thread readding in on this one.)  Thus, since Mayong &amp;quot;was&amp;quot; a demi-plane he was part god and part mortal(well as mortal a vampire can be in norrath...basically he still had a physical body not allowing him to ascend).  When we killed him this allowed him to the status of god and thus he is god Mayong not demi-god mayong.(Correct me if I am wrong here b/c that is what i am readding from the lore posts.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Second and third, Mayong was working for someone.  That is to say he was being inspired by another source and that source is going to eclipse what we have seen thus far.  The only thing that might clash is how much power from this person will be sparred against Mayong.  Remember, Mayong is a god now, and doesn't really need his backer's support.  This would make his power's boundaries limittless b/c Mayong is not bound by the compact made at the Pantheon and, due to his ascension, does not need the powers of the &amp;quot;anonymous&amp;quot; diety to do their bidding anymore b/c he has his own ethereal powers now.  What I see is two things here.  1.  The true deceiver that has spun this web will come out.  This person will probably be Sol Ro, but I am not surprised to see him accompanied with others that helped him, such as Terris-Thule, Luclin, Saryrn.  2.  Mayong striking out on his own and out right defiying the Pantheon Compact and those dietie(s) that helped him to ascend.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lastly, for every counter there is another that will come to bring balance.  Nothing exists without balance and that is proven even with the gods.  Mayong is prone be hurt by bards a lot.  In fact that has been noted in the lore if i'm not mistaken.  Ayonae Ro would seem to be the perfect diety to be Mayong's match here.  So It would not surprise me if Ayonae would be brought in game to to handle Mayong himslef.  Then there is the battle with the Pantheon itself and those that defied the Pact.  You can turn your head to it, but the war of the Pantheon is coming.  Those that helped Mayong, and I say those b/c I believe it has to be more than one to pull this off completely even if it were minor parts with one main orcestrator, will face the other gods and either be punished, stopped, and/or destroyed.  Too many gods are at risk now due to this.  One especially is Brell Serelis.  He is the original diety of the Underfoot, and now that Mayong has ascended, you can bet he will not like that much.  Not too mention, Tunare and Veeshan whom both have their own creations at risks b/c of these events.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is how I see what's about to come.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
