      <description>&lt;div&gt;According to the official lore at&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50054"&gt;http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50054&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Mayong has just ascended to demi-god status with his &amp;quot;death&amp;quot; in the Demi-Plane of Blood. His death as a &amp;quot;mortal&amp;quot; being (being killable and not a godlike being) triggered both his elevation to demi-god status and the completion of the Demi-Plane of Blood as a full realm.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;He was just the Lord of Vampires, dwelling in a near-plane held together by his will and dark magicks. Now, he's a demi-god in a fully realized realm.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;He only seemed like a demi-god before because of all the mystery and legendry he created for himself amongst the various Norrathians and sects of undead. He actually, intentionally and thoroughly, created his own myth to make sure Norrath believed in him as something greater before he actually was. Thus, when he DID become greater, his base of followers and believers was already in place to empower him.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
