      <description>One thing that I find interesting (and applaud SOE for pulling off mostly without a hitch) is how they've adjusted the story line through the years (or at least the DoN and DoDH and PoR stories) to link them all together and to tie in the human nature element that we the players bring in (namely our 'habit' of storming new lands and wrecking our own brand of havoc within them. :) ).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;That was what Venril (and Mayong by way of Venril) was counting on, and it is what Mayong was counting on as well. I suspect people can draw similar linkages throuhg GoD and OoW too.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I think the next big 'challenge' to do will be to come up with a story line that accounts for that behaviour, yet also doesn't leave the player base seeming like they were played for saps (as Mayong played us for his ascension). (And I don't mean any ill about that term; I just couldn't think of a better way to phrase it.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In any case, even though I'm no where near beating Mayong or Vish or Muram, I just wanted to say thanks for how things have been so interconnected lately, and how well everything has been fitting together even with the random player factor. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now lets go kick Mayong's butt again. :)</description>
